-- French Stocks: Nicox, BioMerieux, Technip, Unibail Are Active in Paris
-- Adam Haigh
-- 2010-07-22T07:53:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/french-stocks-nicox-biomerieux-slump-as-technip-unibail-rodamco-rally.html

          
          
             France’s CAC 40 Index lost 0.1
percent to 3,490.06 as of 9:42 a.m. in Paris. The broader SBF
120 Index declined 0.1 percent to 2,595.35.  
 The following stocks are among the most active in the
French equity market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses
after company names.  
 BioMerieux SA (BIM FP) sank 8.8 percent to 81.81 euros, its
biggest drop since July 2004. The company cut its full-year
sales growth target to 6 percent from a previous forecast of
around 7 percent.  
 NicOx SA  (COX FP) slumped 15 percent to 2.42 euros after
U.S. regulators refused to approve its experimental painkiller
naproxcinod.  
 Mersen  (MRN FP) climbed 3.2 percent to 27.35 euros. The
world’s biggest maker of brushes for electrical motors said
second-quarter revenue rose 29 percent. The company reiterated
its targets for 2010 of “organic” sales growth and an increase
in its operating margin before non-recurring items. The company
is considering more “small” acquisitions, Chief Financial
Officer Thomas Baumgartner said.  
 Technip SA  (TEC FP), Europe’s second-largest oilfield-
services provider, rallied 3 percent to 49.95 euros as it
reported a fall in net income to 106 million euros ($135.4
million), beating the 103.7 million-euro average estimate of 11
analysts in a Bloomberg survey.  
 Unibail-Rodamco SE  (UL FP) rose 1.8 percent to 142.55
euros, leading rising shares on the CAC 40 index. Europe’s
largest publicly traded real estate company plans to distribute
1.8 billion euros to investors after it raised cash from
disposals. First-half recurring profit rose 0.4 percent to 4.7
euros a share, it said.  
